===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|bageard||marked by a badge|lang=enm}}, from {{term|bage||badge|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|bage||emblem|lang=xno}}, referring to the animal's badge-like white blaze.

====Noun====
[[Image:Dachs.jpg|thumb|A badger]]
{{en-noun}}

# A common name for any [[mammal]] of three subfamilies, which belong to the family [[Mustelidae]]: [[Melinae]] (Eurasian badgers), [[Mellivorinae]] ([[ratel]] or [[honey badger]]), and [[Taxideinae]] ([[American badger]]).
# A [[native]] or [[resident]] of the American State of [[Wisconsin]].
# {{obsolete}} A brush made of badger hair.
# {{plural|obsolete|vulgar|cant}} A crew of desperate [[villain]]s who robbed near rivers, into which they threw the bodies of those they murdered.

